<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Fort Lauderdale Climate</h2>
<p>For Fort Lauderdale's hot-humid climate, HVAC systems with SEER ratings of 16 or higher are recommended to handle the extended cooling season efficiently. High-efficiency heat pumps are particularly well-suited for the area, as they provide excellent cooling performance while offering energy-efficient heating during the brief winter months when temperatures occasionally drop into the 50s and 60s. Variable-speed systems excel in humid climates like Fort Lauderdale's because they run longer at lower speeds, providing better humidity removal compared to single-stage systems. Since heating needs are minimal‚Äîtypically only 10-15% of total HVAC usage‚Äîthe focus should be on exceptional cooling performance and dehumidification capabilities. Systems with enhanced dehumidification features or separate dehumidifiers are valuable additions, as maintaining indoor humidity levels between 30-50% is crucial for comfort and preventing mold growth in the humid subtropical environment.</p>

